Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on background subtraction, which is a significant component of computer vision systems. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed approach is based on convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach for background subtraction on depth videos. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed method can be used in video surveillance, object tracking, anomaly detection, etc., which are multimedia applications. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed method can be applied to robotics applications, such as autonomous navigation, obstacle detection, etc.
